Package: UpdatedDisperseR
Title: HYSPLIT-Based Air Dispersion and Exposure Modeling
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Djallexi", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "votre@email.com")
Description: Provides functions to run HYSPLIT dispersion simulations in
    parallel, link parcel trajectories to geographic grids, and compute
    population exposure to air pollutants (e.g. SO2). Updated fork of the
    original disperseR package with removed broken dependencies.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
SystemRequirements: HYSPLIT (https://www.ready.noaa.gov/HYSPLIT.php),
    libgfortran3 (Linux uniquement, installable via install_system_deps())
VignetteBuilder: knitr
